  {"t":"h2","text":"Where to stay"},
  {"t":"p","html":"<strong>Mitte</strong> is the easy first-timer base — Brandenburg Gate, Museum Island and the TV Tower are all walkable or a stop away, though it's the most touristy district too. <strong>Kreuzberg</strong> brings street art, multicultural food and late-night bars; <strong>Neukölln</strong> next door is our featured food ground, once overlooked and now genuinely the best-value district for authentic eating (plus Tempelhofer Feld, the old airport-turned-park). <strong>Prenzlauer Berg</strong> is leafy and family-friendly, <strong>Friedrichshain</strong> is the nightlife capital with Berlin's cheapest hostel beds, and <strong>Charlottenburg</strong> is West Berlin elegance with upscale hotels."},
