  {"t":"h2","text":"Getting around"},
  {"t":"p","html":"Berlin Brandenburg Airport (BER) sits about 18km southeast of the center. The Airport Express (FEX) runs every 15 minutes to Hauptbahnhof in roughly 22 minutes, and S-Bahn lines S9 and S45 also connect — S45 conveniently passes through Neukölln and Tempelhof on its way in. The station runs 24/7. Once you're in the city, the BVG network (U-Bahn, S-Bahn, trams and buses) covers everywhere, and Berlin is flat enough to genuinely get around by bike. For Sonnenallee specifically: it has its own S-Bahn station, or take the U7 to Karl-Marx-Straße or Rathaus Neukölln and walk in. Sightseeing hard across several days? The Berlin WelcomeCard bundles unlimited transit with museum and attraction discounts — worth pricing against single tickets before you commit."},
  {"t":"tip","head":"Best time to visit","html":"May through September is the sweet spot — summer highs run 22–25°C, and May, September and early October give you nearly the same mild weather as peak summer minus the July–August crowds. Winter runs genuinely cold (highs near 3°C, snow common December–March), though if Christmas markets are your thing, that's a reason to come anyway."},
